CLASS
--------

    access_modifier class class_name{
      data members;
      constructors;
      methods;
      ...;
    }

 → A class is a blueprint for creating objects.
 → Each class has its methods and attributes that can be accessed and manipulated through the objects.
 → A class contains mainly two things: Methods and Data Members.
 → JVM stores Class structure in Method Area
 → It follows all rules of OOPS concepts

Does a class consume memory?
   Yes. When loaded by JVM, class metadata is stored in the Method Area.
   However, instance variables consume memory only when objects are created in the heap.

Rules :
-There can be only one public class per source file
-The public class name should be the name of the source file
-package statement should be the first statement in the source file
-import statements are present, then they must be written between the package statement and the class declaration.


